BATCH + OpenMP
Mefisto may be executed by BATCH, without visualization.
For example, to mesh, type the command
echo ProjectName; MESHER MeshDataFileName  >ListingOrNot
ou
cd ProjectName | $MEFISTO/pp/ppmail MeshDataFileName
Attention: 99; {Save and Exit}
must be the last option in the file MeshDataFileName
because it is not possible to come back in interative mode.

HEATER:
- Option 12 2D or 3D computation of non zero solutions u of
           -Laplacian u + a1 u + a2 u**2 + a3 u**3 = 0  a3<0
 Attention: gives 4 data games
 game 1: CONDUCTIVITY = 1 in front of -LAPLACIAN u
 game 1: u INITIAL (Example: 1 on a PLSV, 0 else)
 game 2: a1;  game 3: a2; game 4: a3;
 game 1: IMPOSED BOUNDARY CONDITION CONTACT=0
         FLUXES are computed with a conductivity=1
 game 2 3 4: NO BOUNDARY CONDITION to give
- Drawing of the solutions at all steps of time

FLUIDER:
- Solution of the steady or unsteady STOKES problem,
  unsteady NAVIER-STOKES problem for an incompressible
  2D or 3D fluid by Taylor-Hood or Brezzi-Fortin finite
  elements with a skyline storage and CROUT factorization.
- Solution using OpenMP  (execution with threads
  Cf the demand of OMP_NUMBER_THREADS=? of the command
  $MEFISTO/bin/FLUIDER) of the UNSTEADY NAVIER-STOKES
  problem by fractional steps by skyline Cholesky
  factorization or condensed conjugate gradient
  => a lower size of used memory
  with the new boundary condition of the convected velocity of
  a fluid exiting of the domain (option 2 fixed velocity)
- Drawing of particles moving in a flow
- Drawing of the 2d stream function
- Drawing of the velocity norm inside the flow
- Drawing of the pressure on some surfaces of the fluid
- Drawing of the solutions at all steps of time
- A User's updated Manual of Mefisto-FLUIDER is loadable

NLSER:
- Complex solution of the NON-LINEAR SCHRODINGER Equation
  i dU(t)/dt -Alfa Laplacian U(t) + N(t,|U|) U(t) = F(t,X)
  Cf the documentation of the initial menu debunlse.

$MEFISTO/bin.lnx64:
- The libraries contain subroutines fortran.f95 with OpenMP
  directives and executable on multi-processors as
  Intel Core i7 (8 threads maximum)
- The command ended by 77 offers a sequential gfortran
  compilation WITHOUT calls to OpenMP library
  example: $MEFISTO/bin/cbflui77 gives $MEFISTO/pp/ppflui
  a sequential load module for the command FLUIDER
- The command NOT ended by 77 offers a MULTI-THREADS gfortran
  compilation with calls to OpenMP library
  example: $MEFISTO/bin/cbflui gives $MEFISTO/pp/ppflui
  a multi-threads load module for the command FLUIDER

testa: test files
- Flow from 0 to 120 seconds of a 2d or 3d fluid of Reynolds
  number 300 around a roll in a box by Brezzi-Fortin (bf) or
  Taylor-Hood (th) finite elements by conjugate gradient:
  rol2dbfcg, rol3dbfcg,  rol2dthcg,  rol3dthcg 
